wdi-IQ.SCI.SRCE.def: The source data indicator reflects whether a country conducts data collection activities in line with internationally recommended periodicity, and whether data from administrative systems are available. The source data score is calculated as the weighted average of 5 underlying indicator scores. The final source data score contributes 1/3 of the overall Statistical Capacity Indicator score.
wdi-IQ.SCI.SRCE.name: Source data assessment of statistical capacity
wdi-IQ.SCI.SRCE.source: World Bank, Bulletin Board on Statistical Capacity (http://bbsc.worldbank.org).
